episodes.title: Hello
episodes.plot: The Taskmaster challenges a new set of comedians to compete for his golden head.

episodes.title: A Novel About Russian Gulags
episodes.plot: The competition continues as the Taskmaster judges even more Tasks, including one that Joe Thomas describes as 'dehumanising'.

episodes.title: Stuck in a Mammal Groove
episodes.plot: Can the contestants guess what Alex is dressed as? Can they create a volcano? Most importantly, can they apologize for what they've done?

episodes.title: The Barrel Dad
episodes.plot: A hammock-based task threatens to tear the team apart.

episodes.title: Stay Humble
episodes.plot: Herding ping-pong balls, playing catch around the globe and creating food-based injuries are just three of the tasks on offer as the show reaches its halfway point.

episodes.title: Rock 'n' Roll Umlaut
episodes.plot: This week, the comedians are challenged with designing an album cover, scoring a goal, remembering the order of some very special playing cards and hiding in a phone-box.

episodes.title: This Is Trevor
episodes.plot: Can the contestants pick the Pink Ladies? Can they do something powerful with their pinkies? The taskmaster intends to find out.

episodes.title: Aquatic Sewing Machine
episodes.plot: The taskmaster imagines an aquatic trauma when the contestants are asked to bring in the best thing to hold, before an underdog begins to rise through the ranks as the word-based final task approaches.

episodes.title: I've Been a Bit Ill
episodes.plot: The penultimate episode sees the formation of some very strange new people.

episodes.title: Clumpy Swayey Clumsy Man
episodes.plot: Who will take home the coveted 'golden head' trophy in the Taskmaster series 8 finale?
